  <h1>
   math_get_epsilon
  </h1>
  This function will return the current epsilon value for the target platform. For more information on epsilon, please see the function
  <a href="math_set_epsilon.htm">
   <span>
    math_set_epsilon()
   </span>
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">math_get_epsilon();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var e = math_get_epsilon();
if e != 0.000001
{
    math_set_epsilon(0.000001);
}
</code></pre>
  This will retrieve the current epsilon value and store it in a local variable, which is then checked and a new epsilon set if required.
 </body>
</html>